OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1773637426
OL,3,CReeves drawing up plans to help with
OL,4,Cenergy costs as Iran war continues
OL,6,FGas and electricity bills are covered
OL,7,Fby regulator Ofgem's price cap which
OL,8,Fis fixed until June, but if the
OL,9,Fconflict continues and Iran maintains
OL,10,Fits stranglehold on shipping in the
OL,11,FStrait of Hormuz, then, households
OL,12,Fcould face dramatic hikes at that
OL,13,Fpoint.
OL,15,FBut about 1.5 million households
OL,16,Frelying on heating oil already face
OL,17,Fsoaring costs, with the price per
OL,18,Flitre doubling since the start of the
OL,19,Fcrisis.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
